      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is the legal philosophy that the Constitution should be interpreted based on the original public meaning of its text at the time it was adopted. Proponents argue this prevents judges from imposing their personal policy preferences onto the law. By adhering to the original intent, originalism ensures that the Constitution remains a fixed, stable document rather than a constantly evolving political manifesto. This approach is fundamentally about respecting the will of the ratifiers.",
