    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good summary. i've also been reading some critiques that say originalism is just a way for conservative judges to reach specific political outcomes under the guise of legal theory. how do scholars usually respond to the idea that it's more about politics than actual law?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
