      "content": "The perceived one-sidedness in recent Supreme Court decisions is a direct result of the fact that the original public meaning of many foundational texts is inherently ambiguous. When the text is vague, the judges who adhere to originalism are forced to make choices, and those choices inevitably reflect the prevailing conservative worldview of the judges themselves. Therefore, the \"objective\" theory often collapses into a subjective application of historical interpretation when the language itself is not perfectly clear.",
